                                    <p>The tablet is inscribed on <rs type="texts" key="multiple" n=""/><rs type="sides" key="opisthographic">both sides</rs>. Originally opisthographic, although the inscriptions on side B are no longer recognizable. Side A preserves two superimposed inscriptions, 22A and 23A, of which only a small portion of the latter remains visible along the lower edge of the tablet, below the third and final line of 22A. As the editors of <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/></bibl> point out, the cutting lines of the tablet are visible along its upper and lower edges.</p>
                                    <p n="Dialect"><rs type="dialect" ref="#Doric">Doric</rs></p>
